<item>
            <title>[LU-13561] io500 ior_hard_write failed on 2.13.0 with overstripping </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13561</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi!&lt;br/&gt;
We&apos;ve just installed lustre 2.13.0, to set io500 test.&lt;br/&gt;
System contains 2 MDS (4MDT) and 12 OSS (24OST).&lt;br/&gt;
mpirun used on 49 client nodes.&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
For ior_hard test overstripe was set like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lfs setstripe -C $((24*5)) -S 16M $io500_ior_hard&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This test failed with such errors:&lt;br/&gt;
ior ERROR: open64(&quot;/lustre/stor1/rsc/io500/2020-spring/io500.2020.05.15-01.57.48/ior_hard/IOR_file&quot;, 66, 0664) failed, errno 95, Operation not supported (aiori-POSIX.c:413)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe we&apos;ve missed something.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards&lt;/p&gt;</description>
